@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Bobarr" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 4 colours.

                             How to play?

  Gameplay is simple: click on the bar you want to move, if it is
next to the empty space, and the shape of the bar is in line with
it, that bar will move there and its former position will then be
indicated by a coloured rectangular shape, if such a shape was not
already there. In the game, a horizontal bar can move to the left
or right, a vertical bar can move up or down and a diagonal bar can
move diagonally up or down, depending on which "way" it is placed...

  To complicate or simplify your task, pick the one you prefer; a
bar that is located at the edge of the board can move to the other
side if the empty space is located at the other side, and is in
line with that bar.

  Note that you can also use the numbered keys on the numeric
keypad to move the bars, as shown below:

        7         8        9
    upper left   up    upper right

        4                  6
      left               right

        1         2        3
    lower left  down   lower right

  As you move bars, an indicator shows the percentage of bars that
have been moved.

  If you get stuck on one board, or a particular game is impossible
to complete, you can restart the game by clicking on the 'New Game'
button (or by pressing on the 'N' key) and Bobarr will display a
new board.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or by
pressing on the 'Esc' key.

